<div id="review_1169424931" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1169424931" />
    <a title="Sarah" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/36527960-sarah"><img alt="Sarah" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1588539568p2/36527960.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1169424931?book_show_action=true">Jan 15, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sarah" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sarah" href="/user/show/36527960-sarah">Sarah</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1169424931" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1788898301598251294">The use of allegory in this work is simply incredible. The extend to which the technique skillfully formulates and questions each character (power) relation in the text, forcing the reader to engage on ever more multi-facetious levels, only serves to add to the amazement that, in the hundreds of years since this work was written, we have neither surpassed it, nor truly recognised its brilliance. An argument against the period as an intellectual &apos;dark ages&apos; in itself. </span>
  <span id="freeText1788898301598251294" style="display:none">The use of allegory in this work is simply incredible. The extend to which the technique skillfully formulates and questions each character (power) relation in the text, forcing the reader to engage on ever more multi-facetious levels, only serves to add to the amazement that, in the hundreds of years since this work was written, we have neither surpassed it, nor truly recognised its brilliance. An argument against the period as an intellectual 'dark ages' in itself. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1788898301598251294" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


