<div id="review_1710964385" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1710964385" />
    <a title="Beth" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6055877-beth"><img alt="Beth" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1313582790p2/6055877.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1710964385?book_show_action=true">Nov 29, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Beth" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Beth" href="/user/show/6055877-beth">Beth</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6055877-beth?shelf=stuff-i-love">stuff-i-love</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1710964385" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer775197423139099524">I love Piers Plowman. There. I said it. It pulls you in without your realizing that you&apos;ve been pulled in. The poetry is lovely--very good alliterative art--and it adds to the surreal feel of the narrative, which is so vivid that you live it as you read it. The theological and doctrinal points of the poem may not be a modern audience&apos;s cup of tea, but they are well-articulated and they make you think.</span>
  <span id="freeText775197423139099524" style="display:none">I love Piers Plowman. There. I said it. It pulls you in without your realizing that you've been pulled in. The poetry is lovely--very good alliterative art--and it adds to the surreal feel of the narrative, which is so vivid that you live it as you read it. The theological and doctrinal points of the poem may not be a modern audience's cup of tea, but they are well-articulated and they make you think.</span>
  <a data-text-id="775197423139099524" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
